Warning

Special Town Meeting

Thursday May 26, 2016 7:00 p.m.

 

The legal voters of the Town of Bradford, Vermont are hereby notified and
warned to meet at the Bradford Academy Auditorium in Bradford, Vermont on
Thursday May 26, 2016 at 7:00 p.m. to transact the following business:

 

Article 1:  Shall the Town of Bradford purchase a new fire truck to replace
Engine 2, for a price not to exceed $450,000 with up to $190,000 to be used
from the Fire Department Capital Fund and the balance from other funding
sources such as grants, donations, and loans which would be financed over a
period of five years? 

 

Article 2: To authorize the Bradford Public Library to utilize funds
appropriated at the March 2015 Town Meeting for other improvements to the
Library, including funding required to complete the outstanding VCDP
Planning Grant. 

 

Article 3:  To transact any other business that may legally come before the
Special Town Meeting.

 

Article 5:  To adjourn.

 

Dated at Bradford, Vermont, this ______ day of March 2016.

 

_____________________________________________

Thomas E. Unkles, Chair

 

_____________________________________________

Lisa D. Sharp, Vice Chair

 

_____________________________________________

Carole P. Taylor

 

_____________________________________________

Daniel A. Perry III

 

________________________________________

Randy L. Moore

 

I hereby certify that the foregoing Warning was duly recorded before being
posted.

 

 

Attest:  __________________________________, Marianne McClure, Town Clerk

 

Dated at Bradford Vermont this ______ day of March 2016.

 

 

Danielle Robinson

Town of Bradford

Selectboard Administrative Assistant

172 North Main Street

PO Box 339 Bradford, VT 05033

802-222-4727 ext: 304

 

 

 

 

